II/ Java script:
  - check element visible: $('#id').is(":visible")
  - windown resize demo:
      http://jsfiddle.net/UqYCr/
      http://jsfiddle.net/UqYCr/1/
      
  - clientHeight & offsetHeight & scrollHeight:
      refer: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/22675126/what-is-offsetheight-clientheight-scrollheight
      http://jsfiddle.net/shibualexis/yVhgM/3/
      clientHeight: visible height of content + visible padding
      offsetHeight: clientHeight + border + scrollbar
      scrollHeight: clientHeight + non-visible height
      
  - box-model:
      refer: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Box_Model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model
      padding area:
          When the content area has a background, color, or image set on it, this will extend into the padding
          
  - scrollTop & scrollLeft:
      refer: http://www.w3schools.com/jsref/tryit.asp?filename=tryjsref_element_scrollleft
      
  - promise
      https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise
    http://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/ECMA-262.pdf
      
